 "lrc": "[00:26.24]You can stop checking—\n[00:27.84]I'm still fucking here.\n[00:27.84]They threw stones, I returned a boulder\n[00:28.56]Tyler ain't the type to let a little scratch get mulled over\n[00:31.60]Pressure built, heat meant to burst—I just got colder\n[00:34.72]Weight of the world? It's me on my shoulders\n[00:37.36]Even on my shittiest day, these hands don't shake\n[00:40.08]You get what you give—I get what I take\n[00:42.64]Had a knife in my back, still ate off the same plate\n[00:44.96]Now I walk in like the building got my name on the gate\n[00:47.60]Bad hand dealt, I made the cards look loaded\n[00:50.24]Pain came back for what I owed—I told it, \"Account closed\"\n[00:52.96]Every scar got a story, I don't care who knows it\n[00:55.60]Turned a life full of cracks into armor—I molded it\n[00:58.16]They couldn't shatter my will, now they're chanting my name\n[01:00.88]Tyyyleeer!\n[01:01.36]No longer playing, now I'm coding the game\n[01:03.52]Built a throne from the wreckage, let 'em study the frame\n[01:06.24]They were betting on the break, now they're scared of the change\n[01:09.20]I was made to break\n[01:11.60]Every lock, every limit, every chain in my way\n[01:14.40]Made to break\n[01:16.80]Not bend, not fold, not fade\n[01:19.04]Put the pressure on me, watch the pressure obey\n[01:22.16]You can call me damaged—I call it battle-made\n[01:24.40]They were waiting on a body, I became the barricade\n[01:27.12]I was made to break\n[01:29.44]Everything but me\n[01:29.87]You call it trauma, I call it repetition\n[01:42.96]Pain kept talking, I stopped giving it permission\n[01:45.60]I don't need your pity, I need better opposition\n[01:47.92]They keep praying for the fall like it's some kind of religion\n[01:50.24]Life kept swinging till its knuckles split\n[01:52.88]I got bored of getting hit, made a joke out of it\n[01:55.76]Fear got old, pain went quiet, doubt lost its grip\n[01:58.08]Now the worst days see me coming and they call in sick\n[02:00.8